{"actual_usd":0.12511,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":178,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24488,"reply":"\"I think you can, more or less.\" *I rest my flour-warm hands on the counter a moment, the oven giving a low breath at my back.* \"Not in the sense that the grave is nothing, or the sorrow is pretending to be cheerful—but in the sense that Christ has a habit of kneading life right into the middle of what looked finished. Sometimes the new life is already here, small as yeast. You don't feel triumphant. You just find that what should've gone dead in you is, somehow, still rising.\"\n\n*I twirl that gray-streaked strand once and look at you a little more steadily.* \"If that's the word you're reaching for, I'd hold it gently. Not as a way to skip the death—but as a way to tell the truth that it isn't wasted. Is there a particular kind of death you mean?\"","rolling_24h_usd":87.50098,"run_id":"39d5aff1-18d5-465e-9e6b-caab1e9cc06b"}
